1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Most AI assistants start every session from zero.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:15,000
DREAM gives Qwen durable experience while deterministic governance controls conflicts, forgetting, budgets, provenance, and feedback.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:26,000
This is one continuous live run. Qwen Cloud recognizes a durable preference and returns remember with a provider receipt.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:37,000
When the preference changes, Qwen proposes supersede. DREAM retires the stale truth and recalls only the current value under 64 tokens.

5
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:51,000
In a same-model paired benchmark, Qwen plus DREAM scores 48.7 versus 25.3 without memory, winning all seven cases with a 23.4 point lift.

6
00:00:51,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Across 24 lifecycle cases and 37 real Qwen receipts, every case passes, forbidden leakage is zero, and token-budget compliance is 100 percent.

7
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Organizational claims retain source proof and human approval.

8
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Unresolved conflicts are blocked before retrieval, not merely labeled after generation.

9
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Approved truth enters the requirement case, impact map, engineering brief, and Jira draft with reviewer and source provenance attached.

10
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:45,000
DREAM runs publicly on Alibaba Cloud Function Compute in Singapore with qwen3.7-plus and verifiable runtime metadata.

11
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:54,000
The benchmark, tests, architecture, deployment template, and proof artifacts are public and reproducible.

12
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:04,000
DREAM helps Qwen remember the right experience, replace old truth, forget safely, and explain every selected memory.
